{{technical|date=October 2012}}

'''ITAD Subscriber Numbers''', or ISNs, provide a way of interconnecting [[Voice over IP|VOIP]] [[Private branch exchange|PBXs]] by adding a number to the internal phone number of the target phone. The [[Internet Telephony Administrative Domain|ITAD]]<ref>[[Internet Assigned Numbers Authority]], registry of [http://www.iana.org/assignments/trip-parameters/trip-parameters.xml#trip-parameters-5 "TRIP IP Telephony Administrative Domain (ITAD) Numbers"]</ref><ref>RFC 3219</ref> number is added to the target phone number preceded by an asterisk. Therefore, only numbers and symbols which appear on a telephone keypad are used.<ref>Ben Teitelbaum and John Todd, [http://www.freenum.org/cookbook/ "Freenum/ISN Cookbook"], October 2007</ref>

