{{1r|date=May 2015}}A '''multimedia extension connector''' (MXC) is a method of connecting [[video camera]]s and other video inputs to [[video capture card]]s and the like.

MXC is based on the 8-pin [[Mini-DIN connector]]. It is used by [http://www.winnov.com/ Winnov]'s range of Videum capture cards.

