The '''TN 71''' is a [[France|French]]-built [[fusion bomb|thermonuclear warhead]] which was used on submarine-launched ballistic missiles in [[Redoutable-class submarine (1967)|''Redoutable'' class]] ballistic missile submarines.

It has a yield of 150 kt.

Entering service in 1985 on [[M4 SLBM|M4-B ballistic missiles]], it was replaced at the end of October 1996 by the [[TN 75]], which equips [[M45 SLBM|M45 missiles]] for France's [[Le Triomphant class submarine|''Triomphant'' class]] of "new generation" ballistic missile submarines (SNLE-NG).

There were 288 operational TN 71 warheads before its replacement in 1996, and 96 in 2001, but none were remaining by 2004, at which time it was withdrawn from service. 

